claim: Flublok contains 3x the hemagglutinin (HA) antigen content of standard-dose flu vaccines, which has been linked to greater immunogenicity vs standard-dose flu vaccines.
explanation: A flowchart outlining influenza vaccination dosing recommendations for children aged 6 months through 8 years, indicating whether they’ve previously received ≥2 doses of trivalent or quadrivalent influenza vaccine and specifying administration of 1 or 2 doses of the 2022–23 influenza vaccine. The image provides pediatric dosing guidance and makes no reference to Flublok or hemagglutinin antigen content; it does not support the claim. Note: Image appears to be a dosing algorithm with no relevant antigen content data.
